				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="マケランディア (Macelandia)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#177;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#135;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162; (Macelandia) is a team-based strategy simulation card game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players are divided into a light side and a dark side, and fight as a commander who protects the castle and the fortress placed on the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The commander is required to be strategic to utilize the benefits of the land on the vast continent of the Macelandia. Players must deduce from limited information what might be in the enemy's hand. And above all, co-operation with friends is the key to victory. The end of this story is in your hands&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the past, there was a continent called Macelandia in this world. The powers believing in the God of Light and the powers believing in the Dark God fought over and over again across the continent. After a long battle of death, Rumei, the fairy of light, sealed the king of the dark king, Siose, in the cave of The White Nights. This war is called Maceraki War and became a legend.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then after 500 years of peace, the sinister prophecy came to be whispered in the kingdom of acid light Gard. When the moons overlap and the dark king wakes up from a long sleep, he will lead the army of the dark and rise up again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The battle between light and dark, the connection between the two great powers, is about to begin again ...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Macelandia is a strategy simulation card game that realizes a simple but deep game system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player chooses only three actions: attack, reinforcement, and standby. &amp;#10;However, there  are clever rules such as the difference in the role of Castle and Samurai assigned to players, and the Expedition rule, when sending cards to a distance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Elements of strategy, mystery and co-operation are included in simple rules, and 4 to 8 people can enjoy a hot and serious game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you lose, cry out &amp;quot;Macelandia!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;publisher's summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
